# Arquitectura MVVM - Reglas

## Separación de Responsabilidades

### View (Activity/Fragment)
- Solo lógica de UI y navegación
- Observa LiveData del ViewModel
- NO accede directamente a Repository

```kotlin
// ✅ CORRECTO
class AlbumsFragment : Fragment() {
    private val viewModel: AlbumsViewModel by viewModels()
    
    override fun onViewCreated(view: View, savedInstanceState: Bundle?) {
        viewModel.albums.observe(viewLifecycleOwner) { state ->
            when (state) {
                is UIState.Loading -> showLoading()
                is UIState.Success -> showAlbums(state.data)
                is UIState.Error -> showError(state.message)
            }
        }
        viewModel.loadAlbums()
    }
}
```

### ViewModel
- Expone LiveData inmutable
- Transforma datos para la UI
- NO tiene referencias a Views

```kotlin
// ✅ CORRECTO
class AlbumsViewModel(private val repository: AlbumsRepository) : ViewModel() {
    
    private val _albums = MutableLiveData<UIState<List<Album>>>()
    val albums: LiveData<UIState<List<Album>>> = _albums
    
    fun loadAlbums() {
        viewModelScope.launch {
            _albums.value = UIState.Loading
            try {
                _albums.value = UIState.Success(repository.getAlbums())
            } catch (e: Exception) {
                _albums.value = UIState.Error(e.message ?: "Error")
            }
        }
    }
}

// ❌ INCORRECTO - ViewModel con referencia a View
class AlbumsViewModel(private val fragment: AlbumsFragment) : ViewModel()
```

### Repository
- Orquesta fuentes de datos (local/remoto)
- Implementa estrategias de caché
- Retorna modelos de dominio

```kotlin
// ✅ CORRECTO
class AlbumsRepository(
    private val serviceAdapter: AlbumServiceAdapter,
    private val albumDao: AlbumDao
) {
    suspend fun getAlbums(): List<Album> {
        return try {
            val remoteAlbums = serviceAdapter.getAlbums()
            albumDao.insertAll(remoteAlbums.map { it.toEntity() })
            remoteAlbums
        } catch (e: Exception) {
            albumDao.getAll().map { it.toModel() }
        }
    }
}
```

### Service Adapter
- Encapsula llamadas Retrofit
- Convierte DTOs a modelos
- Maneja errores de red

```kotlin
// ✅ CORRECTO
class AlbumServiceAdapter(private val api: VinilosApi) {
    suspend fun getAlbums(): List<Album> {
        return api.getAlbums().map { it.toModel() }
    }
    
    suspend fun createAlbum(album: Album): Album {
        return api.createAlbum(album.toDto()).toModel()
    }
}
```

### DAO (Room)
- Solo operaciones CRUD
- Usa anotaciones @Insert, @Query, etc.

```kotlin
@Dao
interface AlbumDao {
    @Query("SELECT * FROM albums")
    suspend fun getAll(): List<AlbumEntity>
    
    @Insert(onConflict = OnConflictStrategy.REPLACE)
    suspend fun insertAll(albums: List<AlbumEntity>)
}
```

## Flujo de Datos

```
User Action → View → ViewModel → Repository → ServiceAdapter/DAO
                 ↑                    ↓
                 └──── LiveData ←────┘
```

## Anti-Patrones a Evitar

1. ❌ ViewModel accediendo a Context de Activity
2. ❌ Repository con lógica de UI
3. ❌ View llamando directamente a ServiceAdapter
4. ❌ DAO con lógica de negocio
